  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering is complex and involves multiple levels of legislation and regulation:\n\n1. International Level\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- International standards for combating money laundering\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Components\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n- Mandatory reporting for financial institutions\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Transaction monitoring protocols\n\n4. Regulatory Oversight\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Banking regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Government compliance departments\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Civil penalties\n- Fines\n- License revocations\n- International cooperation and information sharing\n\n6. Compliance Obligations\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Staff training\n- Record-keeping\n- Reporting suspicious transactions\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
